Ask HN: Who are the next SBF, Holmes, Milton?
text:
Lately, I've been on a watching spree of videos related to big tech scams, where I noticed a few similarities between the key figures of these scams. Highly charismatic, eccentric, personable.

But with every single one of these personalities, all the signs were there, before their schemes exploded. SBF's persona of a cool gamer guy playing League during investment meetings (and being among lowest ranks possible), Elizabeth Holmes and Trevor Milton not being able to provide much or any proof of their claims.

So the question is, who is next? Who would you bet against, in the short/long run?

HN “***” syndrome and possible cover-up
text:
Three hours ago, noman-land posted about "***" appearing in lieu of a reply's actual text. He was flagged and his post deleted. You can still for the time being catch his post here https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=34694341

I noticed same starting about 6-8 weeks ago. I view posts via the firebase API, so I'm more likely to catch things in an intermediary state. When I view the "***" reply in the browser, the reply body is by then perfectly normal.

title: Ask HN: Is Google CEO worth his price?
text:
Unpopular opinion, not particularly of Google, but what makes a CEO worth millions, magnitude higher than VPs?

They don't have a special degree in CEO science.

Obviously promoting a VP to a CEO is not like upgrading their hardware or doesn't add GPUs to a VP, it is same person with slightly different responsibility and scope.

Wouldn't the CEOs happily take half the price they are getting now and still work? It is not like they can easily get another job worth same compensation.
